txt.en: 9 Honeymead Lane
Talk to Dinodas Boffin on Honeymead Lane
'All right, [placeholder], you go ahead with Dino to Nobottle while I find something I can use to wrap this present. I'll bring it along shortly, but we shouldn't keep Angelica waiting.'
Talk to Prisca Boffin on Honeymead Lane
'DNT - Blah!'
Talk to Bingo Boffin on Honeymead Lane
'Onward, [placeholder], to 9 Honeymead Lane. My sister Angelica will be so pleased!'

'Here we are, [placeholder]. Angelica has done quite well for herself, hasn't she?

'When it comes time for me to find a place of my own, I think I will look for something a little smaller. It seems to me that having so many rooms might invite, well, ghosts! Who needs all those empty rooms, just ripe for haunting? I tell you I do not, but perhaps Angelica isn't worried about that sort of thing. Let's hope she doesn't regret it!

'It is a nice hobbit-burrow, though, I'll say that for her. She knows how to pick them!'
Talk to Angelica Boffin outside her new home
'There's my mother, and Griffo and Esmeralda too.'

'[placeholder]! This is a pleasant surprise! Are you here for my daughter Angelica's house-warming party? You must be, surely!

'I see that some of my children have already arrived. I hope the rest are on their way... sometimes it is hard to keep them on a schedule, the dear ones.

'But this is Angelica's day and I want nothing to spoil it for her!'
Talk to Dinodas outside 9 Honeymead Lane
'Found the place with no trouble, I see, very good.\n\n'And here is the gift for Angelica, perfectly-wrapped, from all her Boffin relatives and from [placeholder] too!'
'Welcome, Bingo, welcome. We shall be quite a merry gathering! I hope there is room enough for all of us inside!'
Bingo has agreed to carry the gift for Angelica so the rest of you can meet up outside her new home.
Bingo Boffin stands on Honeymead Lane with his cousin Prisca and some of her children.

'Oh, hooray, [placeholder]! I didn't know you were going to come to my party! I know it's just a small hobbit-burrow, but it's all mine. I think it is quite cozy!\n\n'Come inside, everyone! I hope there will be room!'
Dinodas and the other Boffins agreed to meet you outside Angelica's new home in Nobottle, on Honeymead Lane.
'There she is!'
Angelica Boffin is delighted to see that you and so much of her family has come to Nobottle to welcome her to her new home.
'Uh... [placeholder]?\n\n'I think I... might have made a mistake.'
Dinodas stands outside Angelica's new home on Honeymead Lane, very pleased with himself.
Prisca Boffin and many of her children gather on Honeymead Lane to welcome Angelica to her new home.
Dinodas stands alone outside 9 Honeymead Lane.
Meet up with the Boffins outside Angelica's new home on Honeymead Lane
Dinodas, Camellia, and Marigold stand outside Angelica's new home
Prisca Boffin, her son Griffo, and her daughter Esmeralda have arrived on Honeymead Lane
Bingo has arrived with the gift for Angelica
'You go ahead with Dino to Nobottle while I find something I can use to wrap this present. I'll bring it along shortly, but we shouldn't keep Angelica waiting.'
Angelica emerges from her new home
All of the Boffins go inside, chatting merrily... except for Dinodas
